#4
In One vs Rest Approach,
One Binary Classifier for each class is made and for each class a logistic regression model is trained.
When a new input is provided ,each classifier outputs a probability and the highest probability is chosen and the output is chosen.

In Softmax (Multinomial) Approach,
One model is trained for all the classes together.This Model calculates a score for every class.
Using the SoftMax function probabilities are obtained for every class using their respective scores.

Differences:

One vs Rest Approach:
1. For each class one binary classifier is trained.
2. One class is treated as positive and all others as negative by the binary classifier.
3. Softmax function is not used.

Softmax (Multinomial) Approach:
1. Only one model is trained for all the classes together.
2. It calculates the probability for every class at the same time.
3. Softmax function is used.


